<subSubSection id="2DD56497FFF7FFBAFF20FB7E612924AD" pageId="3" pageNumber="435" type="description">
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF7FFBAFF20FB7E6191262B" blockId="3.[151,708,1227,1290]" box="[151,404,1264,1290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">
(
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFF28FB7E6136262B" box="[159,307,1264,1290]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1031,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-300@4.[151,1436,1026,1826]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–D. Chanohirata minima A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501290/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Figs. 1. A–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFE89FB7E6189262B" box="[318,396,1264,1290]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,997,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-301@6.[151,1436,991,1935]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Chanohirata minima A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501297/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">3. A–F</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF7FFBAFF20FABF6359266D" blockId="3.[151,1437,1329,2040]" box="[151,860,1329,1356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF7FFBAFF20FABF6146266A" bold="true" box="[151,323,1329,1355]" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Measurement.</emphasis>
Length of male including tegmen: 
<quantity id="A2379AF9FFF7FFBAFD79FABF635D266D" box="[718,856,1329,1356]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="435" unit="mm" value="3.6" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.5">3.5–3.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF7FFBAFF70FADB610326DE" blockId="3.[151,1437,1329,2040]" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF7FFBAFF70FADB614A264E" bold="true" box="[199,335,1365,1391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Coloration.</emphasis>
Vertex pale yellowish, marked with dark brown reticulation and light brown patches, two yellowish brown spots between eyes; eyes grey with brown transverse stripe; ocelli white (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFB81FAF7649526B2" box="[1078,1168,1401,1427]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1031,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-300@4.[151,1436,1026,1826]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–D. Chanohirata minima A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501290/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Face black (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFA84FAF7658B26B2" box="[1331,1422,1401,1427]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1031,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-300@4.[151,1436,1026,1826]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–D. Chanohirata minima A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501290/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Pronotum pale yellowish, marked with dark brown reticulation and yellowish brown patches. Scutellum pale yellowish with dark brown reticulation (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFDD3FA4F62B826FA" box="[612,701,1473,1499]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1031,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-300@4.[151,1436,1026,1826]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–D. Chanohirata minima A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501290/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Forewing subhyaline, with dense and dark brown reticulations (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFF17FA6B60FC26DE" box="[160,249,1509,1535]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1031,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-300@4.[151,1436,1026,1826]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–D. Chanohirata minima A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501290/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF7FFBAFF70F98761E125AE" blockId="3.[151,1437,1329,2040]" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF7FFBAFF70F98761642502" bold="true" box="[199,353,1545,1571]" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Morphology.</emphasis>
Head declivous, including eyes nearly as broad as pronotum; crown medial length 0.4 times width between eyes (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFE3FF9A362152566" box="[392,528,1581,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1031,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-300@4.[151,1436,1026,1826]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–D. Chanohirata minima A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501290/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Figs. 1B, C</figureCitation>
). Postclypeus flat; anteclypeus ridged medially, lateral margins slightly convex, truncate at apex (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFEECF9DF61B3254A" box="[347,438,1617,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1031,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-300@4.[151,1436,1026,1826]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–D. Chanohirata minima A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501290/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Pronotum length 2.0 times medial length of crown. Scutellum length 0.7 times medial length of pronotum (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFEC8F9FB61D325AE" box="[383,470,1653,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1031,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-300@4.[151,1436,1026,1826]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–D. Chanohirata minima A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501290/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF7FFBAFF70F917612924AD" blockId="3.[151,1437,1329,2040]" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF7FFBAFF70F917617C2592" bold="true" box="[199,377,1689,1715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore longer than high, with short and long macrosetae near posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFA82F917658A2592" box="[1333,1423,1689,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,997,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-301@6.[151,1436,991,1935]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Chanohirata minima A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501297/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Valve triangular. Subgenital plate extending beyond apex of pygofer, nearly triangular, with sparsely distributed setae on ventral side (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFE25F96F61EE25DA" box="[402,491,1761,1787]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,997,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-301@6.[151,1436,991,1935]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Chanohirata minima A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501297/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Style with developed preapical lobe, apical apophysis pointed, fingerlike, curved laterally; preapical lobe with several setae near inner margin (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFCF3F88B639E243E" box="[836,923,1797,1823]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,997,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-301@6.[151,1436,991,1935]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Chanohirata minima A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501297/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Connective ‘Y’-shaped, stem slightly longer than anterior arms (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFED8F8A761CD2462" box="[367,456,1833,1859]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,997,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-301@6.[151,1436,991,1935]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Chanohirata minima A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501297/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft slender, with two pairs of processes, lateral flange triangular, near apex, and with smaller process on apex, dorsal apodeme plate-like, well-developed, preatrium reduced, gonopore apical (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF7FFBAFF28F8FF611A24AD" box="[159,287,1905,1932]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,997,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-301@6.[151,1436,991,1935]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–F. Chanohirata minima A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501297/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="435">Figs. 3E, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
